# Interpreter for '_batch2()' function (batch command execution)
# Terminal function that executes batch files and displays progress/results
#
# Default value: "cat"
#   Displays batch execution progress and results without re-executing output
#   The _batch2() function outputs:
#     - Progress messages (# Executing:, # ✓ Success, # ✗ Failed)
#     - Output from delegated commands (via process_arguments())
#     - Summary (# Batch execution complete)
#
# The batch command executes its input commands via process_arguments(),
# which already applies the appropriate interpreter to each delegated command.
# The output should be displayed directly to the user, not executed again.
#
# Using 'sh' here would cause the system to try executing the output text
# (including config filenames, validation symbols, etc.) as shell commands,
# leading to errors like "sh: wireguard/wg-TEST-CH-1.conf: not found".
#
# Phase 3.4: Fixed protocol-agnostic list/validate delegation issues
# Architecture fix: Renamed from ___batch2 to _batch2 (terminal function)
